    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Discretization error is below the 5% threshold, output comparison shows NIH predictions within 14.7% of experimental data across all operating points, and validation activities are directly relevant to the COU. Six factors are not assessed, which is acceptable per ASME V&V 40 at Model Risk Level 2 for a Class II device. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied at all 5 assessed operating points. The credibility assessment supports the decision to accept the CFD model for identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions in the CPB COU.",
